Definition: vocally expressing grief or sorrow or resembling such expression
Example: lamenting sinners; wailing mourners; the wailing wind; wailful bagpipes; tangle her desires with wailful sonnets- Shakespeare
Synonyms: wailing, wailful, vocally, expressing, grief, or, sorrow, resembling, such, expression, sinners, mourners, the, wind, bagpipes, tangle, her, desires, with, sonnets, -, Shakespeare
Category: adj.all
